label.value: increased protein localization to chromatin during cellular response to hydroxyurea

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin is increased during a cellular response to hydroxyurea.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein ubiquitination during cellular response to hydroxyurea

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the ubiquitination of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during a cellular response to hydroxyurea.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the G1 to G0 transition is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to tolnaftate. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of tolnaftate that allows wild type cells to grow.

A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to econazole. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of econazole that allows wild type cells to grow.

A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to diethylstilbestrol. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of diethylstilbestrol that allows wild type cells to grow.
A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing tolnaftate.
A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing econazole.
A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing diethylstilbestrol.

A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to L-arginine. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of L-arginine that allows wild type cells to grow.

A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to chaetoglobosin D. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of chaetoglobosin D that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: decreased cell population growth on serine nitrogen source

value.value: A vegetative cell population phenotype in which cell growth is decreased relative to normal in a medium containing serine as the nitrogen source.

label.value: cell cycle arrest in mitotic G1 phase in response to pheromone without starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the occurrence of cell cycle arrest in response to a pheromone occurs in G1 phase, but in the absence of starvation (i.e., in nutrient-rich conditions, under which wild-type fission yeast cells do not arrest).

A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of DNA binding at a Mlu1 cell cycle box (MCB) by a gene product is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). The relevant gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

A molecular function phenotype in which DNA binding at an RNA polymerase II proximal promoter that contains a Mlu1 cell cycle box (MCB) by a gene product does not occur, when a gene or the bound DNA sequence is mutated. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mitotic chromosome condensation begins earlier than normal.

label.value: premature protein localization to mitotic spindle pole body during metaphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the mitotic spindle pole body that normally occurs in anaphase instead begins in metaphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to mitotic spindle pole body during anaphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the mitotic spindle pole body is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during anaphase.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which septation initiation network signaling is abnormal SIN signaling is mediated by the small GTPase Ras, and results in the initiation of contraction of the contractile ring at the beginning of cytokinesis and cell division by septum formation.

label.value: septation initiation network signaling from both mitotic spindle pole bodies

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which septation initiation network signaling takes place at both mitotic spindle pole bodies. Normally, SIN signaling occurs only at the new SPB.

A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cortical endoplasmic reticulum (ER) organization is abnormal. Cortical ER organization results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of the part of the endoplasmic reticulum that consists of highly dynamic tubules that are juxtaposed to the plasma membrane.

label.value: cortical endoplasmic reticulum detached from plasma membrane

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the cortical endoplasmic reticulum (ER) is dissociated from the plasma membrane. Normally, cortical ER tubules are closely juxtaposed to the plasma membrane.

label.value: premature actomyosin contractile ring contraction with increased contraction rate

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which actomyosin contractile ring contraction begins earlier than normal and the rate, or speed, of ring contraction is increased.

label.value: decreased duration of protein localization to mitotic spindle pole body

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which one or more proteins is localized to the mitotic spindle pole body for a shorter time than normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased duration of protein localization to medial cortical node

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which one or more proteins is localized to the medial cortical nodes for a shorter time than normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which vacuole fission, i.e. the division of one vacuole into two or more separate vacuoles, is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to actin cytoskeleton

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the actin cytoskeleton is abnormal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to actin cytoskeleton during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the actin cytoskeleton is abnormal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal medial membrane band sterol distribution

value.value: A localization phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the distribution of sterols in the medial membrane band is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: decreased protein localization to mitotic spindle pole body during anaphase B

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the mitotic spindle pole body is decreased during anaphase B of mitosis.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased septation initiation network signaling during anaphase B

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which septation initiation network signaling occurs to a lower extent than normal during anaphase B of the mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: increased duration of septation initiation network signaling

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the duration of septation initiation network signaling is longer than normal. Signaling may continue after cytokinesis takes place.

label.value: decreased protein localization to cytoplasm during mitotic telophase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cytoplasm is decreased during telophase of mitosis.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: multiseptate vegetative cell with normal cell length

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cell length is normal, and the cell contains more than one septum.

A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which septation initiation network signaling begins earlier than normal. Signaling may begin in interphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: abnormal medial membrane band sterol distribution

value.value: A localization phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the distribution of sterols in the medial membrane band is abnormal.
A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the endosome(s) is abnormal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to late endosome

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to late endosomes does not occur.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a protein that is not normally found in endosomes is observed there.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which mitophagy, i.e. autophagic degradation of the mitochondria, is abnormal.
A cellular process phenotype in which mitophagy, i.e. autophagic degradation of the mitochondria, is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
A cellular process phenotype in which mitophagy, i.e. autophagic degradation of the mitochondria, is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation.
A cellular process phenotype in which mitophagy, i.e. autophagic degradation of the mitochondria, is abnormal when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation.
A cellular process phenotype in which mitophagy, i.e. autophagic degradation of the mitochondria, does not occur when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation.
A cellular process phenotype in which mitophagy, i.e. autophagic degradation of the mitochondria, is increased when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation.
A cellular process phenotype in which mitophagy, i.e. autophagic degradation of the mitochondria, is decreased when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation.

A molecular function phenotype in which CLRC complex binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant does not occur. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

label.value: abolished chromatin silencing at ectopic tethering site

value.value: A transcription regulation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which chromatin silencing does not occur at a site where silencing can normally be triggered by the ectopic tethering of a protein.

definition.value: Note that this term incorporates some information about experimental tools, but is included to allow effects of tethering different (wild-type or mutated) proteins to the binding site to be represented. The tethering site is placed adjacent to a reporter gene that is expressed in the absence of a binding domain fusion (i.e. in a region not normally silenced).

label.value: increased chromatin silencing at ectopic tethering site

value.value: A transcription regulation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which chromatin silencing is increased at a site where silencing can be triggered by the ectopic tethering of a protein.

definition.value: Note that this term incorporates some information about experimental tools, but is included to allow effects of tethering different (wild-type or mutated) proteins to the binding site to be represented. The tethering site is placed adjacent to a reporter gene that is expressed in the absence of a binding domain fusion (i.e. in a region not normally silenced).

label.value: decreased protein localization to mitochondrial outer membrane

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the mitochondrial outer membrane is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.
